    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Front Cover and Related Components -
        Removal - Gerotor Assembly Oil Pump
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="6">
        <title>Gerotor Assembly Oil Pump</title>
        <figure id="f2650617.5" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh13/H13018.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Removing the front oil seal</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove front oil seal with a heel bar while oil pump housing assembly is still attached to
                front cover. Discard the front oil seal.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650618" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh13/H13013.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil pump housing mounting bolt locations</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt, M8 x 60 (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Dowels (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt, M8 x 25 (4)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove two bolts (M8 x 60) retaining the oil pump housing cover.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove four bolts (M8 x 25) retaining the oil pump housing cover.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650619" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figEg8/EG8654.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil pump housing cover</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil pump housing seal</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Outer rotor</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove oil pump housing cover and discard oil pump housing seal.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650620" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8651.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Removing the vibration damper key</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using a hammer and chisel, tap the vibration damper key out of the crankshaft. Exercise
                caution not to mark the crankshaft or distort the keyway groove.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650621" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8657.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Washer seal and inner rotor</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the washer seal and inner rotor.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Mark the gerotor oil pump assembly with a permanent marker if pump is to be returned to
                service. The mark is to indicate the inner and outer rotor relationship to each other and orientation to
                the front cover. Remove oil pump gerotor assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650623" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh13/H13012.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil pump housing plate and seal</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil pump housing seal</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil pump housing plate</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove oil pump housing plate and discard seal.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Refer to the
                <hotlnk document="eges2651_S26509101.xml" xrefid="S26509101" appearance="hottext">disassembly of
                    crankshaft oil pump drive (spline)
                </hotlnk>
                for procedure relating to oil pump drive.
            </para>
        </step1>
